
[1]alledge

   ALLEDGE', v.t. [L. allego, ad and lego, to send; Eng. lay.]

   1. To declare; to affirm; to assert; to pronounce, with positiveness;
   as, to alledge a fact.

   2. To produce as an argument, plea or excuse; to cite or quote; as, to
   alledge the authority of a judge.
